data.chText: （表示厌烦、失望等）该死，他妈的，讨厌
data.enText: a swear word that people use to show that they are annoyed, disappointed, etc.

data.chText: 真该死！我把他要来这事儿给忘了。
data.enText: Oh damn! I forgot he was coming.
damned

data.chText: （表示厌烦）可恶的，讨厌的，该死的
data.enText: a swear word that people use to show that they are annoyed with sb/sth

data.chText: 这该死的东西就是发动不起来！
data.enText: The damned thing won't start!

data.chText: 他真是个该死的讨厌鬼！
data.enText: He's a damn nuisance!

data.chText: （抱怨时用）倒霉事一桩接一桩
data.enText: used to complain that a lot of unpleasant things keep happening to you
used when swearing at sb/sth to show that you are angry

data.chText: 你这个浑蛋！我决不让你欺负我。
data.enText: Damn you! I'm not going to let you bully me.

data.chText: 这该死的机器！怎么就是无法运行？
data.enText: Damn this machine! Why won't it work?
to decide that sb must suffer in hell

data.chText: 强烈指责；谴责；狠狠批评
data.enText: to criticize sb/sth very strongly

data.chText: 这部影片因无谓的暴力受到评论家的强烈指责。
data.enText: The film was damned by the critics for its mindless violence.
damn the consequences, expense, etc.

data.chText: 置后果（或费用等）于不顾
data.enText: used to say that you are going to do sth even though you know it may be expensive, have bad results, etc.

data.chText: 管它花多少钱，咱们先庆祝一番再说！
data.enText: Let's celebrate and damn the expense!
damn sb/sth with faint praise

data.chText: 用冷漠的赞扬贬低；寓贬于褒；名褒实贬
data.enText: to praise sb/sth only a little, in order to show that you do not really like them/it
I'll be damned!

data.chText: （表示惊奇）真没想到，真叫我吃惊
data.enText: used to show that you are very surprised about sth
I'm damned if…
used to show that you refuse to do sth or do not know sth
I'm damned if I'll apologize!
I'm damned if I know who he is.
as near as damn it/dammit
used to say that an amount is so nearly correct that the difference does not matter
It will cost £350, or as near as dammit.

data.enText: You know damn well (= you know very well) what I mean!

value.def: Damn ,damn it, and dammit are used by some people to express anger or impatience.

example.ex: Don't be flippant, damn it! This is serious.
example.tran: 别不当回事，该死！这可不是闹着玩儿的事。

value.tran: (表示愤怒或不耐烦)该死，可恶，他妈的

value.def: Damn is used by some people to emphasize what they are saying.

example.ex: There's not a damn thing you can do about it now.
example.tran: 现在你对此做什么都完全无济于事。

example.ex: As it turned out, I was damn right...
example.tran: 结果证明我百分百正确。

example.ex: Let's have a damn good party.
example.tran: 我们来搞一个超棒的聚会吧。

value.tran: (用于加强语气)该死的，可恶的，十足的，完全的

value.def: If you say that a person or a news report damns something such as a policy or action, you mean that they are very critical of it.

example.ex: ...a sensational book in which she damns the ultra-right party.
example.tran: 她在其中大力鞭挞该极右党派的耸人听闻的书

example.ex: ...a report damning the chocolate advertising people for targeting women in their campaigns.
example.tran: 谴责巧克力广告企划人员在宣传中以女性为目标人群的一份报告

value.def: If you say that someone does not give a damn about something, you are emphasizing that they do not care about it at all.
People use damn near to emphasize that what they are saying is not actually true, but is very close to being true.

example.ex: That's a question damn near every woman who ever lived has had to answer for herself.
example.tran: 那几乎是每个有过生活经历的女人都必须要自己回答的问题。

value.def: Some people say as near as damn it or as near as dammit to emphasize that what they have said is almost completely accurate, but not quite.

example.ex: It's as near as damn it the same thing...
The stadium will be as near as dammit empty.
example.tran: 体育场里将几乎空无一人。

trans: 非常愚蠢的;愚蠢至极的
